   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE THE LIVING IN THE BODY Scripture Reading: Col 1:18; Eph 4:15-16; Rom 12:5; Eph 5:23-24; 1 Tim 5:17a; 1 Cor 3:10a; Heb 13:17; 2 Cor 3:17; Rom 8:11, 13; Phil 1:8; 1 Cor 12:25b-26 OUTLINE Living corporately with the members under the Head Col 1:18: Having the Head as the life, the principal object, and the center Eph 4:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Coordinating with the members to live a life which expresses the Head Rom 12:5.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Authority in the Body: The authority of the Head flowing throughout the Body Eph 5:23-24.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The deputy authorities carrying out the authority of the Head: There being elders in the local churches 1 Tim 5:17a.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>There being leading co-workers in the work 1 Cor 3:10a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>All the members submitting directly to the Head Eph 5:24a.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>At the same time all the members also submitting to the deputies of the Head Heb 13:17.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The authority of the Spirit and the Body: The Spirit being the embodiment of the Head 2 Cor 3:17.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The Spirit living and moving in the members Rom 8:11, 13.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The members' feeling for the Body: Taking the Head's feeling as their own feeling Phil 1:8.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>In the principle of caring for the Body 1 Cor 12:25b-26.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>In mind, thoughts, words, and actions, taking the Body as the rule, with no separation or disconnection from the Body.</S>
   </TEXT>
